first_para: Catherine McKinnell (born 8 June 1976) is a British Labour Party politician who has been the Member of Parliament (MP) for Newcastle upon Tyne North since 2010. She was elected with 40.8% of the vote, and a majority of 3,414 over her Liberal Democrat rival.

full.extract:
Catherine McKinnell (born 8 June 1976) is a British Labour Party politician who has been the Member of Parliament (MP) for Newcastle upon Tyne North since 2010. She was elected with 40.8% of the vote, and a majority of 3,414 over her Liberal Democrat rival.
^ "Two North East MPs standing down". BBC News. 4 July 2009. 
^ "Election 2010 - Newcastle-upon-Tyne North". BBC News. Retrieved 7 May 2010.
full.title: Catherine McKinnell
